# Links sample

Exercises `textDocument/definition`. Put the cursor on a link and jump to
its target.

- Explicit anchor link: [go to Targets](#Targets)
- Implicit heading reference: [Targets][]
- Reference link: [the manual][manual]
- Link to an attributed block: [see the note](#important-note)
- Cross-file (not resolved yet): [other doc](outline.dj#Usage)
- External (ignored): [djot](https://djot.net)

[manual]: https://example.com/manual

## Targets

This heading's auto id is `Targets`.

{#important-note}
This paragraph carries an explicit `{#important-note}` id, so it is a jump
target too.
